  "instructions": [
    "1. Slice the pork into thin strips and season with salt.",
    "2. In a large skillet, heat the vegetable oil over medium-high heat.",
    "3. Add the pork and cook until browned, about 3-4 minutes.",
    "4. Add the onion and bell pepper to the skillet and cook until tender.",
    "5. Add the garlic, soy sauce, sugar, and tangy sauce to the skillet and stir to combine.",
    "6. Add the velvety sauce to the skillet and stir to combine.",
    "7. Reduce heat to medium-low and simmer for 10-15 minutes.",
    "8. Serve hot over rice or noodles.",
    "9. Garnish with chopped scallions, if desired.",
    "10. Serve immediately and enjoy."
